{
  "uuid": "8cd27e2049a5b863299bf5dbb8bfbd56",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Furniture Retail Sales Executive",
  "description": "<h4>Job Offers &amp; Benefits:</h4>\n<p>· <strong>Basic Salary &amp; same work month commission transfer</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>Total sales payout on tiered commission &amp; incentives.</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>Variable performance bonus and conditional leave encashment.</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>Incremental annual leave yearly (12 to 18 days)</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>Staff credit for free product and discount on product purchase yearly.</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We are looking for a <strong>team player</strong> to join our growing Singapore Furniture Brand. We are keen to learn and improve from your contribution to our mutual success.</p>\n<h4><strong>Candidate Role:</strong></h4>\n<p>Provide customers with good service and soft sell effectively.</p>\n<h4>Job Scope:</h4>\n<p>· Actively seek out customers, to greet and thank warmly every walk-in customer.</p>\n<p>· Provide pleasant, professional product advice to customer without hard selling.</p>\n<p>· Identify needs to recommend appropriate products and promote product features.</p>\n<p>· Tabulate customers preferences, questions and competitor’s product, pricing and promo.</p>\n<p>· Provide follow up on customer’s enquiries, deliveries, issues and payment matters.</p>\n<p>· Design &amp; update product price tags and promotion materials on displayed products.</p>\n<p>· Ensure products are well displayed and maintain store cleanliness.</p>\n<p>· Make presentation videos for sales and promotion of products.</p>\n<p>· Participate in ad hoc duties being assigned and sometimes cover different branches.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>v <strong>Consistent able to achieve average of $75,000 monthly sales and above.</strong></p>\n<p>v <strong>Able to focus multiple walk-ins to close key products, cross sell bundles and add-ons.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>v Able work 5/6 alternating days a week, compulsory on weekends. </strong></p>\n<p>v Work 8 hours with 1 hour meal break for standard shift or extended shift occasionally.</p>\n<p>v Basic understanding of sales principles and customer service practices.</p>\n<p>v Strong communications, presentation and interpersonal skills.</p>\n<p>v Friendly, enthusiastic and pro-active personality.</p>\n<p>v Interest to read up relevant product background and build knowledge to be able to give correct advice to customers.</p>\n<p>v Minimum higher secondary, ‘N/O’ level certification or 1 Year retail sales experience.</p>\n<p>v Competent in MS Office and able to use / learn Brochure Design Tools is a plus.</p>\n<p>v Keen in Home Furnishing &amp; Decoration knowledge is advantageous.</p>",
